------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation.

The Acro installation process is described in a file in this directory
named INSTALL.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Overview.

The principle directories contained in this distribution are

bin			Executables used to configure/compile Acro.

config			Files used by the configure process.

doc			Documentation about Acro.  See below.

include			A common directory where package include directories
			are linked

lib			A common directory where package libraries are linked

packages		The directories of Acro packages

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies.

Acro is not strictly dependent on any external software packages.
The parallel solvers are dependent on MPI (using the mpich library).
There are a variety of external libraries integrated into Acro.
There exist COLIN interfaces to commercial packages like DOT, and the
COIN library includes interfaces to commercial LP solvers.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Platforms.

This package is quite generic and thus it should compile on a wide range
of platforms.  Acro actively supported with nightly build verifications
on the following platforms for the given operating systems, C++ compilers,
and MPI libraries:

  SUN      Solaris 2.8            CC v5.4              MPICH/SUNWhpc

  PC       Red Hat LINUX 9        g++ v3.2.2           MPICH IP/GM

  SGI      IRIX 6.5               CC v7.41             SGI MPI

  DEC      OSF 5.1                cxx v6.3-002         Digital MPI

  IBM      AIX 5.1                xlC v6               POE MPI

  TFLOP    Cougar   (compute)     ciCC v4.4.0          MPICH
           TFLOP OS (service)     iCC  v4.4.0          MPICH

Ports to the following platforms are also available although they are
not actively maintained:

  Cplant   Cplant OS (compute)    c++                  MPICH
           LINUX     (service)    g++                  MPICH

  PC       Windows (via Cygwin)   g++                  MPICH

  Mac      OSX (Darwin)           g++                  MPICH

  HP       HP-UX 10.20            CC                   -

Currently, the presence of gmake is required to successfully compile
the Acro package on HP, SGI, DEC, and IBM platforms.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation.

Two forms of documentation are supported: html and pdf.  The main html page
can be accessed at doc/uguide/html/index.html.

The pdf version of the User Manual is available at doc/uguide/userman.pdf.gz.

This documentation provides an abbreviated users guide (which needs
more work), as well as extensive source-level documentation generated
with doxygen.  Additionally, online documentation is available at
http://software.sandia.gov/Acro.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WARNING.

Many packages in Acro are "research" codes, and thus Acro is
the subject of continuing active development.  Bug reports, suggestions
for improvement, and required changes for other machines/compilers
are welcome.  Direct all messages to acro-developers@software.sandia.gov.
